#!/usr/bin/env bun
// Package-owned entry script for the workflow-process child.
//
// The supervisor resolves this path via `require.resolve` /
// `import.meta.resolve` and hands it to its `subprocessSpawner`
// callback. The script's runtime body -- env parse, IPC channel
// open, RepoStore construction, `runWorkflowChild` invocation --
// is the next commit's responsibility. The file exists in this
// commit so the path is resolvable from `WorkflowSupervisorBindings.
// binaryPath` against a real install on disk.
//
// Until the body lands, an accidental invocation exits non-zero with
// a message naming the missing implementation. The supervisor's
// production wiring will be paired with the implementation in the
// same release; an invocation that lands on this stub indicates a
// release-coordination bug the operator should hear about loudly.
process.stderr.write(
  "workflow-host: bin/workflow-child invoked before runWorkflowChild has landed\n",
);
process.exit(78); // EX_CONFIG: configuration error
